1
00:00:26,192 --> 00:00:27,318
Ms. Kiryu.

2
00:00:27,402 --> 00:00:28,361
Please sign this.

3
00:00:28,445 --> 00:00:29,446
Okay.

4
00:00:37,579 --> 00:00:39,581
You look like you don't get it at all.

5
00:00:39,664 --> 00:00:41,458
- No, I'll check it.
- Thank you.

6
00:00:41,541 --> 00:00:43,752
This too, please.
April's post-mortem reports.

7
00:00:43,835 --> 00:00:45,754
And here is the summary
of the test results.

8
00:00:46,337 --> 00:00:47,172
Got it.

9
00:00:47,255 --> 00:00:48,840
- Thank you.
- Thank you.

10
00:00:49,424 --> 00:00:51,176
Will you really be okay?

11
00:00:51,259 --> 00:00:52,886
Yes, it's no problem at all.

12
00:00:52,969 --> 00:00:53,928
Of course it isn't.

13
00:00:54,012 --> 00:00:56,514
Ms. Kiryu is the head of MEJ, after all.

14
00:00:56,598 --> 00:00:57,557
Right?

15
00:00:57,640 --> 00:00:58,641
Yes.

16
00:01:01,728 --> 00:01:03,688
Here is the summary
of the chemical analysis.

17
00:01:03,772 --> 00:01:05,065
Please sign it.

18
00:01:10,820 --> 00:01:12,530
I'm going to step out for a bit.

19
00:01:12,614 --> 00:01:15,075
My boss at the Ministry of Health
is calling for me.

20
00:01:16,534 --> 00:01:18,244
- She ran away.
- She certainly did.

21
00:01:22,749 --> 00:01:26,461
Regarding that youth poverty support
project you were moving forward with,

22
00:01:26,544 --> 00:01:28,087
it is finally ready to launch.

23
00:01:28,171 --> 00:01:29,297
What?

24
00:01:29,380 --> 00:01:30,423
Really?

25
00:01:30,507 --> 00:01:33,676
However, since you are busy
with the MEJ now,

26
00:01:33,760 --> 00:01:36,638
I have decided to put
another person in charge of it.

27
00:01:36,721 --> 00:01:37,555
What?

28
00:01:37,639 --> 00:01:39,349
Keep up the good work over there.

29
00:01:57,784 --> 00:01:58,827
Is something wrong?

30
00:01:58,910 --> 00:01:59,869
Well…

31
00:01:59,953 --> 00:02:02,831
It seems your hands have stopped moving.

32
00:02:03,706 --> 00:02:05,708
Oh, yes, they have.

33
00:02:06,584 --> 00:02:10,296
I'm just stamping seals. I'll be fine.
I'll finish it after this all-nighter.

34
00:02:10,380 --> 00:02:12,048
I wouldn't recommend that.

35
00:02:12,132 --> 00:02:14,509
Staying up all night
is the same as being drunk.

36
00:02:15,385 --> 00:02:16,219
Drunk?

37
00:02:16,302 --> 00:02:18,972
Cognitive function
after 24 hours without sleep

38
00:02:19,055 --> 00:02:22,600
is reportedly at the same level
as a blood alcohol concentration

39
00:02:22,684 --> 00:02:24,102
of 0.10 percent.

40
00:02:24,185 --> 00:02:27,522
Information cannot be retained
by the brain in that state.

41
00:02:27,605 --> 00:02:29,566
But I won't finish unless I work
all night.

42
00:02:29,649 --> 00:02:33,194
That said, research shows that women
who sleep for less than four hours

43
00:02:33,278 --> 00:02:36,573
have twice the mortality risk
compared to sleeping seven hours.

44
00:02:36,656 --> 00:02:39,909
By pulling an all-nighter,
you think you're increasing your time,

45
00:02:39,993 --> 00:02:43,746
but you might actually be decreasing it.

46
00:02:45,748 --> 00:02:47,292
I will be careful.

47
00:02:47,375 --> 00:02:48,459
As much as I can.

48
00:02:48,543 --> 00:02:49,377
Okay then!

49
00:02:54,215 --> 00:02:55,216
Hello.

50
00:02:55,300 --> 00:02:56,384
Good evening.

51
00:02:56,467 --> 00:02:58,219
It happened in the owner's room.

52
00:02:58,303 --> 00:02:59,470
This way.

53
00:03:02,599 --> 00:03:04,851
The victim is 39-year-old Hayato Kuriyama.

54
00:03:04,934 --> 00:03:06,311
The owner of this club.

55
00:03:06,394 --> 00:03:10,273
A host from a partner club found the body
when he came for a meeting.

56
00:03:17,822 --> 00:03:21,409
Fine white froth is visible
around the nose and mouth.

57
00:03:21,492 --> 00:03:23,620
There is a possibility of drowning.

58
00:03:23,703 --> 00:03:24,537
Drowning?

59
00:03:24,621 --> 00:03:27,373
You mean he drowned inside a closet?

60
00:03:27,457 --> 00:03:30,710
It would be difficult to kill him outside
and move him here.

61
00:03:30,793 --> 00:03:33,254
But drowning inside a room?

62
00:03:33,338 --> 00:03:36,758
It is possible as long as there is enough
water to cover the mouth and nose.

63
00:03:45,350 --> 00:03:48,811
The autopsy shows
that the cause of death was drowning.

64
00:03:48,895 --> 00:03:50,146
Components of the cleaning agent

65
00:03:50,230 --> 00:03:52,982
used in the room's toilet were
detected in the water inside the lungs.

66
00:03:53,066 --> 00:03:57,237
We found pressure marks on the neck
and a slight bruise on the head.

67
00:03:57,320 --> 00:03:58,947
Both occurred while he was alive.

68
00:03:59,030 --> 00:04:00,907
We also found skin fragments

69
00:04:00,990 --> 00:04:03,159
under his fingernails
that don't belong to Mr. Kuriyama.

70
00:04:03,243 --> 00:04:04,452
Testing revealed

71
00:04:04,994 --> 00:04:07,538
that it is female DNA.

72
00:04:09,457 --> 00:04:10,917
Female…

73
00:04:11,000 --> 00:04:14,295
Did the victim
have any trouble with women?

74
00:04:14,379 --> 00:04:17,590
When he took a liking to a girl,
he would try to keep her for himself.

75
00:04:17,674 --> 00:04:19,300
They were too scared to refuse.

76
00:04:19,384 --> 00:04:21,469
Some girls were backed into a corner.

77
00:04:21,552 --> 00:04:24,347
Had he been clashing
with anyone in particular lately?

78
00:04:30,019 --> 00:04:31,229
Well, actually,

79
00:04:32,230 --> 00:04:35,066
<i>one girl was arguing with him</i>
<i>about breaking up.</i>

80
00:04:41,781 --> 00:04:42,991
Excuse me.

81
00:04:44,325 --> 00:04:45,410
Police.

82
00:04:48,538 --> 00:04:49,706
Police?

83
00:04:49,789 --> 00:04:53,126
Could you come with us to the station
to discuss Hayato Kuriyama?

84
00:04:53,209 --> 00:04:54,794
I'm sorry.

85
00:04:54,877 --> 00:04:57,422
I have to go to work now.

86
00:04:58,089 --> 00:05:01,634
Female DNA was detected on the body.

87
00:05:11,811 --> 00:05:15,815
Will you cooperate with a DNA test?

88
00:05:21,988 --> 00:05:23,448
I'm sorry.

89
00:05:27,327 --> 00:05:29,120
I'm sorry.

90
00:05:31,998 --> 00:05:33,458
<i>The culprit is 24-year-old</i>

91
00:05:33,541 --> 00:05:35,626
Miyuki Yanagihara,
an employee at the club.

92
00:05:35,710 --> 00:05:39,547
She visited the victim's room
on the day of the crime.

93
00:05:40,131 --> 00:05:42,008
Please just let me go.

94
00:05:45,178 --> 00:05:46,804
I'm at my limit.

95
00:05:56,105 --> 00:05:57,565
I'll kill you if you run away.

96
00:06:27,136 --> 00:06:29,764
<i>She put poison in his protein shake</i>
<i>and left the room.</i>

97
00:06:30,681 --> 00:06:31,641
<i>However…</i>

98
00:06:31,724 --> 00:06:33,142
Where's your earring?

99
00:06:33,226 --> 00:06:34,060
What?

100
00:06:37,772 --> 00:06:38,689
One second.

101
00:07:28,489 --> 00:07:31,868
So then, she strangled the victim
after he regained consciousness.

102
00:07:36,539 --> 00:07:39,750
<i>After that,</i>
<i>fearing he would wake up again,</i>

103
00:07:39,834 --> 00:07:41,836
<i>she submerged his face in the toilet.</i>

104
00:07:48,634 --> 00:07:49,719
What?

105
00:07:49,802 --> 00:07:52,889
But no poison was detected
in the autopsy, was it?

106
00:07:52,972 --> 00:07:55,892
The components checked
in the initial screening are limited.

107
00:07:55,975 --> 00:08:00,521
Irregular toxins won't be detected
unless we specifically test for them.

108
00:08:00,605 --> 00:08:01,439
Test for them?

109
00:08:01,522 --> 00:08:04,066
What was the substance used?

110
00:08:04,692 --> 00:08:08,237
She's actually remaining silent
about the poison.

111
00:08:08,905 --> 00:08:10,114
<i>What poison was it?</i>

112
00:08:11,365 --> 00:08:13,075
Where did you get it?

113
00:08:16,537 --> 00:08:18,080
I forgot.

114
00:08:18,164 --> 00:08:19,207
What?

115
00:08:19,290 --> 00:08:20,374
Why?

116
00:08:21,167 --> 00:08:22,919
Maybe she's protecting someone.

117
00:08:23,002 --> 00:08:26,255
In that case, finding the toxin
could be quite difficult.

118
00:08:26,339 --> 00:08:29,634
For now, let's broaden
the scope of the analysis.

119
00:08:29,717 --> 00:08:30,843
- Okay.
- Okay.

120
00:08:30,927 --> 00:08:33,679
We will investigate
the source of procurement as well.

121
00:08:36,265 --> 00:08:37,099
Hello?

122
00:08:38,976 --> 00:08:40,603
Huh? What do you mean?

123
00:08:43,606 --> 00:08:44,649
I'll be right back.

124
00:08:46,776 --> 00:08:47,818
What happened?

125
00:08:49,111 --> 00:08:51,531
A staff member from the club
turned himself in.

126
00:08:54,200 --> 00:08:57,119
He says he was the one
who killed the owner.

127
00:09:04,710 --> 00:09:06,671
I'm the one who did it.

128
00:09:07,255 --> 00:09:10,091
That day, I went
to talk to him about a loan.

129
00:09:10,591 --> 00:09:11,801
Please, I beg you!

130
00:09:12,426 --> 00:09:14,011
Are you stupid?

131
00:09:20,643 --> 00:09:21,811
Bastard!

132
00:09:35,408 --> 00:09:37,910
<i>After that, I got scared</i>

133
00:09:37,994 --> 00:09:39,412
and ran away.

134
00:09:40,037 --> 00:09:44,125
But then I saw on the news
that Miyuki had been arrested.

135
00:09:44,875 --> 00:09:46,335
It was all my fault.

136
00:09:47,461 --> 00:09:49,380
Miyuki is innocent.

137
00:09:49,463 --> 00:09:51,257
Please, arrest me now!

138
00:09:51,340 --> 00:09:52,383
Mr. Murano.

139
00:09:53,467 --> 00:09:56,846
Did you really kill him by strangulation?

140
00:09:57,638 --> 00:09:58,598
Yes.

141
00:10:02,143 --> 00:10:04,604
She has already admitted to the crime.

142
00:10:04,687 --> 00:10:07,189
That's impossible! Please, investigate!

143
00:10:07,273 --> 00:10:08,274
Like I said…

144
00:10:08,357 --> 00:10:10,234
Where is the ashtray you used to hit him?

145
00:10:10,318 --> 00:10:11,360
Hey.

146
00:10:12,069 --> 00:10:13,613
I threw it into the Ooguri River.

147
00:10:17,491 --> 00:10:19,577
Why did you ask about the murder weapon?

148
00:10:19,660 --> 00:10:22,246
The bruise on the top of the victim's head

149
00:10:22,330 --> 00:10:25,625
might have been caused
by Murano hitting him.

150
00:10:25,708 --> 00:10:29,086
If we find the weapon and match it,
we can be certain.

151
00:10:29,170 --> 00:10:33,841
Wasn't that just from bumping into
something when dragging him around?

152
00:10:33,924 --> 00:10:36,302
Besides, the cause of death
was drowning, right?

153
00:10:36,385 --> 00:10:40,598
Murano's statement
that he strangled him doesn't add up.

154
00:10:40,681 --> 00:10:43,809
It's only natural to consider
Miyuki Yanagihara as the culprit.

155
00:10:43,893 --> 00:10:47,938
Murano is just giving a false confession
to protect Miyuki Yanagihara.

156
00:10:48,022 --> 00:10:49,440
Miyuki is innocent.

157
00:10:49,523 --> 00:10:51,150
Please, arrest me now!

158
00:10:51,233 --> 00:10:54,153
However, as long as
no poison has been detected,

159
00:10:54,236 --> 00:10:57,114
we should investigate
assuming every possibility.

160
00:10:57,198 --> 00:11:00,660
Let's investigate their relationship and
search for the murder weapon.

161
00:11:00,743 --> 00:11:02,662
- Supervisor.
- Yes?

162
00:11:02,745 --> 00:11:05,498
The cause of death
has been determined to be drowning.

163
00:11:05,581 --> 00:11:08,876
There's no need for the MEJ
to investigate any further, is there?

164
00:11:09,835 --> 00:11:11,671
Oh, well…

165
00:11:12,797 --> 00:11:15,883
The MEJ has the authority to conduct
all general investigations to--

166
00:11:15,966 --> 00:11:18,260
Do you have anything else
besides "authority"?

167
00:11:19,011 --> 00:11:21,430
How can you call yourself the supervisor?

168
00:11:23,057 --> 00:11:24,016
Let's go.

169
00:11:24,100 --> 00:11:24,934
Yes, ma'am!

170
00:11:28,521 --> 00:11:31,357
We have no choice but to move on our own.

171
00:11:32,441 --> 00:11:36,278
Could you investigate the relationship
between Yanagihara and Murano?

172
00:11:36,862 --> 00:11:38,739
What? Me?

173
00:11:38,823 --> 00:11:41,492
I will proceed
with identifying the poison.

174
00:11:41,575 --> 00:11:43,244
I'm counting on you.

175
00:11:53,170 --> 00:11:54,880
Are we looking for it after all?

176
00:11:54,964 --> 00:11:58,217
We were told the weapon was thrown away,
so we have no choice.

177
00:11:59,468 --> 00:12:01,387
Here I thought I could go home today.

178
00:12:01,470 --> 00:12:03,347
I wanted to finish early too.

179
00:12:03,431 --> 00:12:04,849
Do you have any plans?

180
00:12:04,932 --> 00:12:06,183
I do.

181
00:12:06,267 --> 00:12:07,393
I'm getting snacks,

182
00:12:07,476 --> 00:12:10,479
watch a reality-TV show
while drinking wine, and doze off.

183
00:12:10,563 --> 00:12:12,690
Wait. Ms. Dojima, you watch dating shows?

184
00:12:13,274 --> 00:12:14,191
I do.

185
00:12:14,275 --> 00:12:17,987
Wow, you're actually interested in love
and things like that?

186
00:12:20,072 --> 00:12:23,576
Even I have interests in things
that aren't violent and terrible.

187
00:12:39,175 --> 00:12:40,176
We're taking a break!

188
00:12:40,259 --> 00:12:41,719
We're taking a break.

189
00:12:49,727 --> 00:12:52,188
I mean, how long are we going to do this?

190
00:12:54,148 --> 00:12:56,692
The culprit is Miyuki Yanagihara.

191
00:12:56,775 --> 00:12:59,153
We're not going to find that ash tray!

192
00:13:01,614 --> 00:13:04,366
Something's bothering me.

193
00:13:05,034 --> 00:13:08,454
Nothing came up in the gas chromatography
or liquid chromatography.

194
00:13:08,954 --> 00:13:11,332
Capillary chromatography is also negative.

195
00:13:12,374 --> 00:13:13,542
Damn it!

196
00:13:14,251 --> 00:13:17,046
We'd have no trouble
if she just said what it was.

197
00:13:17,129 --> 00:13:18,839
I wonder why she won't.

198
00:13:18,923 --> 00:13:21,550
Maybe that club staff member
got it for her.

199
00:13:22,510 --> 00:13:25,804
I think she's staying silent
to protect him.

200
00:13:25,888 --> 00:13:28,599
So they're both covering for each other?

201
00:13:28,682 --> 00:13:29,475
Exactly.

202
00:13:29,558 --> 00:13:33,646
Is there a possibility that there was
no poison in the first place?

203
00:13:33,729 --> 00:13:36,398
Kuriyama had pulmonary edema.

204
00:13:36,482 --> 00:13:41,195
While it's a finding seen in drowning,
it can also occur in drug poisoning.

205
00:13:41,820 --> 00:13:45,991
We cannot deny the possibility that
some kind of drug was ingested.

206
00:13:47,159 --> 00:13:48,994
I'm asking again.

207
00:13:49,662 --> 00:13:52,289
How did you get the poison?

208
00:13:54,875 --> 00:13:56,794
Why won't you tell me?

209
00:14:01,674 --> 00:14:04,426
You're protecting someone, aren't you?

210
00:14:05,970 --> 00:14:06,929
A lover…

211
00:14:08,472 --> 00:14:09,390
perhaps?

212
00:14:15,563 --> 00:14:20,484
Were Miyuki and Murano possibly
dating in secret, without telling anyone?

213
00:14:20,568 --> 00:14:22,862
No, I can't imagine they were.

214
00:14:23,821 --> 00:14:25,531
The owner would have them killed.

215
00:14:27,408 --> 00:14:30,244
When did Miyuki start working at the club?

216
00:14:30,828 --> 00:14:32,454
About a year ago, I think.

217
00:14:32,538 --> 00:14:34,957
She had money problems
and was looking for a new job.

218
00:14:35,040 --> 00:14:37,918
What kind of person was Murano?

219
00:14:38,002 --> 00:14:39,587
He was actually a former host.

220
00:14:39,670 --> 00:14:43,340
He was working at an affiliate club
and moved here.

221
00:14:43,424 --> 00:14:45,718
Do you know the name of that host club?

222
00:14:49,263 --> 00:14:50,681
Supervisor!

223
00:14:51,390 --> 00:14:52,308
Why are you here?

224
00:14:53,601 --> 00:14:55,895
To interview involved parties.

225
00:14:55,978 --> 00:14:57,438
Without telling the police?

226
00:14:57,521 --> 00:14:58,856
It was Dr. Masumi's instruction.

227
00:14:58,939 --> 00:15:01,317
You just do whatever
people tell you, don't you?

228
00:15:01,400 --> 00:15:02,484
Excuse me.

229
00:15:07,323 --> 00:15:08,616
A host club?

230
00:15:09,575 --> 00:15:11,410
So that's your hobby?

231
00:15:12,161 --> 00:15:14,997
No! It's Murano's former workplace.

232
00:15:15,664 --> 00:15:17,666
I thought I might learn something.

233
00:15:22,838 --> 00:15:24,465
Are you coming?

234
00:15:24,548 --> 00:15:25,382
What?

235
00:15:26,175 --> 00:15:29,345
You'll just move around secretly
on your own anyway, right?

236
00:15:32,514 --> 00:15:35,392
Murano was a good guy.
He wasn't suited to being a host.

237
00:15:35,476 --> 00:15:38,520
Had you heard anything from Murano?

238
00:15:38,604 --> 00:15:41,065
About trouble with the owner,

239
00:15:41,148 --> 00:15:44,401
or about a hostess
named Miyuki Yanagihara?

240
00:15:46,153 --> 00:15:48,405
I'm not sure.

241
00:15:51,951 --> 00:15:53,035
It's 100,000?

242
00:15:53,118 --> 00:15:55,621
- One of those then.
- What?

243
00:15:55,704 --> 00:15:58,082
Champagne coming up!

244
00:15:58,165 --> 00:16:00,250
Thank you, welcome to the club!

245
00:16:00,334 --> 00:16:02,044
- Welcome!
- Welcome!

246
00:16:02,127 --> 00:16:03,253
All right!

247
00:16:03,837 --> 00:16:05,047
Thanks.

248
00:16:06,715 --> 00:16:08,592
What? Aren't the police
supposed to pay this?

249
00:16:08,676 --> 00:16:11,845
You're the supervisor, right?
Figure it out with your budget.

250
00:16:13,514 --> 00:16:16,767
Want to go get food?
I'll at least make that my treat.

251
00:16:18,310 --> 00:16:19,645
Let's go.

252
00:16:25,275 --> 00:16:27,361
NO DRUGS TARGETED FOR SCREENING DETECTED

253
00:16:35,119 --> 00:16:38,163
Getting a hostess job
because of financial trouble, huh?

254
00:16:38,247 --> 00:16:42,209
Many young people can't earn enough
even if they work full-time

255
00:16:42,292 --> 00:16:45,045
due to non-regular employment
and low wages.

256
00:16:45,129 --> 00:16:47,631
So they end up in the nightlife business.

257
00:16:47,715 --> 00:16:49,508
You're surprisingly well-informed.

258
00:16:49,591 --> 00:16:51,927
Originally, I wanted to
work in social welfare

259
00:16:52,011 --> 00:16:54,471
because I wanted to help those people.

260
00:16:54,555 --> 00:16:56,098
Before coming to MEJ,

261
00:16:56,181 --> 00:16:58,809
I was in youth poverty support
for a long time.

262
00:16:59,560 --> 00:17:02,896
Why is someone as noble as you
the MEJ supervisor?

263
00:17:02,980 --> 00:17:06,358
Poverty support and
the cause of death are totally different.

264
00:17:12,990 --> 00:17:14,366
You got transferred.

265
00:17:16,785 --> 00:17:17,619
Yes.

266
00:17:21,457 --> 00:17:25,210
Of course, I intend to work
as hard as I can in any way I can.

267
00:17:26,628 --> 00:17:27,838
But, to be honest,

268
00:17:28,714 --> 00:17:31,050
I still want to return to the MHLW.

269
00:17:35,637 --> 00:17:37,222
That might be perfect, actually.

270
00:17:37,765 --> 00:17:38,682
What?

271
00:17:39,475 --> 00:17:43,145
If you've done that kind of work,
don't you understand how she feels?

272
00:17:43,979 --> 00:17:44,855
You know,

273
00:17:45,481 --> 00:17:47,858
she has stopped talking to the police.

274
00:17:49,568 --> 00:17:51,403
Why don't you try talking to her?

275
00:17:57,659 --> 00:17:59,703
My name is Kiryu from MEJ.

276
00:18:01,872 --> 00:18:03,540
We're an MHLW organization

277
00:18:03,624 --> 00:18:06,001
that specializes in determining
causes of death.

278
00:18:07,836 --> 00:18:09,755
No matter how many times you ask,

279
00:18:10,839 --> 00:18:12,841
I don't remember anything
about the poison.

280
00:18:19,723 --> 00:18:21,225
Are you protecting Murano?

281
00:18:23,560 --> 00:18:24,770
Murano?

282
00:18:26,522 --> 00:18:29,191
What has he got to do with it?

283
00:18:30,692 --> 00:18:31,777
Actually,

284
00:18:33,195 --> 00:18:35,114
Murano turned himself in.

285
00:18:39,034 --> 00:18:39,952
What?

286
00:18:48,252 --> 00:18:52,464
What was your relationship with Murano?

287
00:18:54,550 --> 00:18:55,801
Murano…

288
00:18:57,678 --> 00:18:59,972
was always supporting me.

289
00:19:04,101 --> 00:19:07,354
I started this job
to pay back my student loans.

290
00:19:08,605 --> 00:19:10,315
I've always regretted it.

291
00:19:11,984 --> 00:19:13,193
Student loans?

292
00:19:13,986 --> 00:19:16,113
My family was poor.

293
00:19:16,780 --> 00:19:19,241
I went to a beautician school
on a scholarship.

294
00:19:22,161 --> 00:19:24,997
But the salary
for an assistant was low, so…

295
00:19:27,916 --> 00:19:30,252
I started a part-time job
at a hostess club.

296
00:19:31,003 --> 00:19:32,754
You don't have to worry anymore.

297
00:19:34,298 --> 00:19:37,134
Some girls work only until
they've paid back their scholarships.

298
00:19:39,678 --> 00:19:41,221
Thank you very much.

299
00:19:42,389 --> 00:19:43,599
<i>But in the end,</i>

300
00:19:44,391 --> 00:19:46,143
I was forced to become his mistress.

301
00:19:49,396 --> 00:19:50,856
Before I knew it…

302
00:19:52,941 --> 00:19:54,693
I had nowhere else to go

303
00:19:55,611 --> 00:19:57,529
and no place to return to.

304
00:19:58,989 --> 00:20:02,117
<i>I had no choice</i>
<i>but to rely on that man to live.</i>

305
00:20:05,412 --> 00:20:06,705
And during that time…

306
00:20:07,331 --> 00:20:09,166
I'm here for you.

307
00:20:10,500 --> 00:20:13,128
<i>…Murano encouraged me.</i>

308
00:20:14,087 --> 00:20:16,590
I had to do my best to get out of there…

309
00:20:19,134 --> 00:20:21,595
and started to believe that I could.

310
00:20:23,639 --> 00:20:24,640
But…

311
00:20:30,687 --> 00:20:32,940
How did it end up like this?

312
00:20:37,236 --> 00:20:40,447
<i>So they were dating after all.</i>

313
00:20:41,240 --> 00:20:42,282
Probably.

314
00:20:44,034 --> 00:20:45,118
Also,

315
00:20:45,202 --> 00:20:48,664
it doesn't seem they coordinated
their stories and turned themselves in.

316
00:20:48,747 --> 00:20:50,999
When I told her Murano
had turned himself in,

317
00:20:51,083 --> 00:20:53,710
Miyuki looked genuinely surprised.

318
00:20:54,211 --> 00:20:56,755
It didn't seem like she knew beforehand.

319
00:20:57,631 --> 00:21:01,260
Then Murano really was
protecting Yanagihara?

320
00:21:03,470 --> 00:21:05,681
That might be true.

321
00:21:12,980 --> 00:21:13,814
What's wrong?

322
00:21:18,443 --> 00:21:20,445
My family was poor too,

323
00:21:20,946 --> 00:21:23,699
and I went to university
thanks to a scholarship.

324
00:21:24,825 --> 00:21:27,327
I joined the MHLW

325
00:21:27,411 --> 00:21:31,581
because I wanted to help people
like myself move forward, but…

326
00:21:33,125 --> 00:21:34,501
In my current position,

327
00:21:35,294 --> 00:21:36,670
I can't do anything.

328
00:21:42,759 --> 00:21:44,469
Is that really true?

329
00:21:47,723 --> 00:21:49,266
Even in your current position,

330
00:21:49,933 --> 00:21:51,643
isn't there something you can do?

331
00:21:53,186 --> 00:21:56,189
That's what you worked so hard for
at the Ministry, isn't it?

332
00:22:06,616 --> 00:22:07,743
Also,

333
00:22:08,368 --> 00:22:10,037
there's something bothering me.

334
00:22:11,788 --> 00:22:14,833
When her arm was grabbed by the victim,

335
00:22:15,375 --> 00:22:17,377
he apparently called her "Mari."

336
00:22:18,170 --> 00:22:19,254
Mari?

337
00:22:25,886 --> 00:22:27,012
Mari…

338
00:22:27,637 --> 00:22:28,680
What?

339
00:22:30,348 --> 00:22:31,433
Mari…

340
00:22:34,936 --> 00:22:38,774
<i>To have to depend on someone</i>
<i>who gets your name wrong…</i>

341
00:22:40,400 --> 00:22:43,236
<i>She felt pathetic</i>
<i>for having to live like that.</i>

342
00:22:48,116 --> 00:22:49,618
<i>She said that before she knew it,</i>

343
00:22:50,118 --> 00:22:52,245
<i>she was strangling him.</i>

344
00:22:54,414 --> 00:22:57,084
Maybe she was just at her limit.

345
00:22:57,167 --> 00:22:59,878
The victim laid hands on many women.

346
00:22:59,961 --> 00:23:01,296
She might be one of them.

347
00:23:02,964 --> 00:23:05,634
It might have something
to do with the case.

348
00:23:05,717 --> 00:23:07,260
I'll look into it.

349
00:23:23,568 --> 00:23:24,694
Let's get married.

350
00:23:25,987 --> 00:23:27,114
It's impossible.

351
00:23:28,323 --> 00:23:29,407
We can't escape.

352
00:23:33,203 --> 00:23:35,205
If only he wasn't here,

353
00:23:37,457 --> 00:23:40,127
I could be with the person I love forever.

354
00:23:57,144 --> 00:24:00,272
<i>Even in your current position,</i>
<i>isn't there something you can do?</i>

355
00:24:02,107 --> 00:24:04,609
I had to do my best to get out of there…

356
00:24:13,285 --> 00:24:14,369
All right.

357
00:24:24,379 --> 00:24:25,213
What…

358
00:24:27,883 --> 00:24:29,467
You were working until morning?

359
00:24:30,093 --> 00:24:31,511
As you can see.

360
00:24:32,470 --> 00:24:35,307
So, did you find any poison?

361
00:24:35,390 --> 00:24:36,308
No.

362
00:24:37,058 --> 00:24:39,895
I've tried a thousand patterns,

363
00:24:40,437 --> 00:24:43,523
but the parameter settings
are still infinite.

364
00:24:48,945 --> 00:24:49,863
Yes?

365
00:24:49,946 --> 00:24:51,406
Ms. Dojima, it's an emergency!

366
00:24:51,489 --> 00:24:54,576
The ashtray believed to be
the murder weapon has been found!

367
00:24:56,411 --> 00:24:58,371
The shape of the discovered ashtray

368
00:24:58,455 --> 00:25:00,957
matches the wound on Kuriyama's head.

369
00:25:01,041 --> 00:25:03,168
Murano's fingerprints
were also detected on the ashtray.

370
00:25:03,919 --> 00:25:06,087
What about
Miyuki Yanagihara's fingerprints?

371
00:25:06,171 --> 00:25:07,464
None of hers.

372
00:25:07,964 --> 00:25:11,635
So the culprit really was
Murano after all?

373
00:25:11,718 --> 00:25:12,636
Yes.

374
00:25:12,719 --> 00:25:15,639
The prosecution has also decided
to indict Murano.

375
00:25:16,723 --> 00:25:18,058
Please wait.

376
00:25:18,141 --> 00:25:19,768
The cause of death was drowning.

377
00:25:19,851 --> 00:25:23,104
Murano's statement says
that he strangled him. It doesn't add up.

378
00:25:23,188 --> 00:25:24,648
We know that.

379
00:25:25,732 --> 00:25:28,735
But evidence backing the crime
has surfaced.

380
00:25:28,818 --> 00:25:31,905
According to the police,
it appears that Murano is the culprit.

381
00:25:32,405 --> 00:25:35,116
The investigation task force
is being disbanded.

382
00:26:01,476 --> 00:26:02,727
Wait!

383
00:26:39,764 --> 00:26:42,142
The mystery has not yet been solved.

384
00:26:43,810 --> 00:26:46,354
What poison did Miyuki administer,

385
00:26:47,314 --> 00:26:51,443
and why does Murano's statement
differ from the cause of death?

386
00:26:53,987 --> 00:26:55,739
I'm going to the scene again.

387
00:26:56,406 --> 00:27:00,076
There might be a piece
we haven't found yet.

388
00:27:05,915 --> 00:27:06,750
Okay!

389
00:27:12,464 --> 00:27:14,341
We're going to
Miyuki Yanagihara's apartment.

390
00:27:14,424 --> 00:27:15,550
What?

391
00:27:15,633 --> 00:27:18,887
We can't just let it end
like this either, can we?

392
00:27:20,680 --> 00:27:21,765
Yes, ma'am!

393
00:27:46,456 --> 00:27:47,540
Cute.

394
00:27:48,249 --> 00:27:50,251
Did it belong to the victim, you think?

395
00:28:05,266 --> 00:28:06,559
Hey, you!

396
00:28:07,644 --> 00:28:09,396
- Wait!
- Stop!

397
00:28:14,025 --> 00:28:15,735
Did you find something?

398
00:28:16,778 --> 00:28:19,864
No, nothing in particular.

399
00:28:22,867 --> 00:28:23,952
Doctor,

400
00:28:24,035 --> 00:28:26,246
that pen is bothering you, right?

401
00:28:26,329 --> 00:28:29,791
Compared to the victim's
other belongings, it's quite different.

402
00:28:29,874 --> 00:28:32,419
I wonder why. It's a mystery.

403
00:28:32,502 --> 00:28:33,920
Dr. Masumi,

404
00:28:34,003 --> 00:28:37,465
no toxins were detected
in the line test either.

405
00:28:38,049 --> 00:28:39,509
Okay.

406
00:28:39,592 --> 00:28:42,887
Let's go back to basics and start over
from the elemental analysis.

407
00:28:42,971 --> 00:28:44,097
Okay.

408
00:28:45,932 --> 00:28:46,891
It's Mari-chan!

409
00:28:48,101 --> 00:28:49,060
Mari-chan?

410
00:28:49,644 --> 00:28:50,812
<i>Magical Detective Mari.</i>

411
00:28:50,895 --> 00:28:52,647
It's a new popular anime.

412
00:28:52,731 --> 00:28:53,982
Oh, okay.

413
00:28:57,736 --> 00:29:00,488
Is this girl called "Mari"?

414
00:29:01,072 --> 00:29:01,865
Yes.

415
00:29:02,741 --> 00:29:03,825
Is something wrong?

416
00:29:03,908 --> 00:29:08,204
When the victim woke up,
he apparently called Miyuki "Mari."

417
00:29:08,288 --> 00:29:13,209
The police couldn't find any Mari
who knew the victim.

418
00:29:13,293 --> 00:29:16,921
But surely, it couldn't be
an anime character, right?

419
00:29:22,844 --> 00:29:24,846
I found out the name of the poison.

420
00:29:25,555 --> 00:29:26,723
What is it?

421
00:29:28,349 --> 00:29:29,309
Aconitine.

422
00:29:31,478 --> 00:29:33,396
Of course, we wouldn't find that.

423
00:29:33,480 --> 00:29:35,523
We don't usually test for that.

424
00:29:35,607 --> 00:29:37,442
I'll cross-reference it with the database.

425
00:29:37,525 --> 00:29:38,735
Wait.

426
00:29:39,944 --> 00:29:42,280
We did not find aconitine in the body.

427
00:29:44,407 --> 00:29:46,034
The pieces might be

428
00:29:46,868 --> 00:29:48,536
coming together.

429
00:29:56,753 --> 00:30:00,173
Regarding the poison
you said you gave to Kuriyama,

430
00:30:00,256 --> 00:30:04,010
no matter how much we investigated,
it could not be detected.

431
00:30:05,512 --> 00:30:07,847
However, that was only natural.

432
00:30:09,057 --> 00:30:12,727
Kuriyama had not ingested poison
in the first place.

433
00:30:13,978 --> 00:30:15,730
What do you mean?

434
00:30:17,106 --> 00:30:19,776
I put poison in his drink.

435
00:30:19,859 --> 00:30:24,781
I heard you were called
"Mari" by the victim.

436
00:30:25,740 --> 00:30:27,200
What about it?

437
00:30:27,283 --> 00:30:30,620
Do you know who Mari is?

438
00:30:33,164 --> 00:30:35,834
I don't know.
Just some other woman, right?

439
00:30:35,917 --> 00:30:38,461
I thought so too at first.

440
00:30:38,545 --> 00:30:40,964
But no matter how much we investigated,

441
00:30:41,047 --> 00:30:44,384
we could not find any woman named Mari.

442
00:30:45,009 --> 00:30:47,554
The only Mari found…

443
00:30:48,638 --> 00:30:49,848
was this girl.

444
00:30:51,015 --> 00:30:52,350
From an anime?

445
00:30:53,184 --> 00:30:55,103
Her name is Mari,

446
00:30:55,687 --> 00:30:57,105
from <i>Magical Detective Mari.</i>

447
00:30:58,273 --> 00:31:02,026
Kuriyama was a die-hard fan
of this character.

448
00:31:03,236 --> 00:31:07,448
You're saying I was mistaken
for an anime character?

449
00:31:07,532 --> 00:31:08,491
Yes.

450
00:31:09,242 --> 00:31:11,077
When we examined the hippocampus,

451
00:31:11,160 --> 00:31:13,371
the part of the brain
which governs memory,

452
00:31:13,454 --> 00:31:15,748
we saw necrosis in the surrounding area.

453
00:31:15,832 --> 00:31:16,916
In other words,

454
00:31:17,542 --> 00:31:19,919
Kuriyama suffered
a consciousness disorder,

455
00:31:20,003 --> 00:31:23,715
and as a result,
he mistook you for his beloved Mari.

456
00:31:25,174 --> 00:31:29,095
That's because of the poison, right?

457
00:31:29,178 --> 00:31:30,305
No.

458
00:31:30,388 --> 00:31:33,641
Because the poison you used

459
00:31:34,142 --> 00:31:35,810
was aconitine.

460
00:31:39,230 --> 00:31:43,860
The person who purchased
the poison for you told us.

461
00:31:44,444 --> 00:31:45,278
What?

462
00:31:46,988 --> 00:31:47,989
Of course,

463
00:31:48,573 --> 00:31:51,492
you know who that person is.

464
00:31:51,576 --> 00:31:56,080
You've been silent all this time
to protect him, haven't you?

465
00:32:00,501 --> 00:32:01,920
The one who bought the poison

466
00:32:02,712 --> 00:32:03,755
was the host…

467
00:32:06,758 --> 00:32:07,884
Kaito Miura.

468
00:32:07,967 --> 00:32:10,595
No! I bought it myself!

469
00:32:10,678 --> 00:32:13,681
Kaito Miura has already
admitted his involvement.

470
00:32:15,058 --> 00:32:18,227
I was worried there was evidence left
of me buying that poison,

471
00:32:18,311 --> 00:32:20,855
so I went and checked Miyuki's place.

472
00:32:20,939 --> 00:32:23,858
Does that mean you also had
a grudge against Kuriyama?

473
00:32:23,942 --> 00:32:27,153
He found out I was trying to
go independent and was interfering.

474
00:32:27,236 --> 00:32:30,698
But I only bought the poison,
Miyuki is the one who did it.

475
00:32:30,782 --> 00:32:33,910
I won't be charged with murder, right?

476
00:32:36,746 --> 00:32:38,414
It's not Kaito's fault.

477
00:32:40,291 --> 00:32:41,793
I just asked him.

478
00:32:41,876 --> 00:32:44,170
He has nothing to do with it!

479
00:32:44,253 --> 00:32:48,841
You put the aconitine purchased
by Mr. Miura into the protein.

480
00:32:48,925 --> 00:32:51,511
However, if aconitine is ingested,

481
00:32:51,594 --> 00:32:55,556
brain function is instantly destroyed,
so one would never regain consciousness.

482
00:32:55,640 --> 00:32:57,809
So, a disturbance of consciousness

483
00:32:57,892 --> 00:33:00,645
and mistaking you for Mari,
is not possible.

484
00:33:02,021 --> 00:33:03,690
That doesn't make sense.

485
00:33:04,273 --> 00:33:06,901
Then why did the owner collapse?

486
00:33:06,985 --> 00:33:11,864
That's because Kuriyama
had people trying to kill him twice.

487
00:33:12,949 --> 00:33:14,075
Twice?

488
00:33:14,659 --> 00:33:17,829
<i>That day, another person had visited</i>
<i>the owner's room</i>

489
00:33:18,413 --> 00:33:22,000
<i>between when you mixed the poison</i>
<i>into the drink</i>

490
00:33:22,583 --> 00:33:25,670
and you returning
to retrieve your earring.

491
00:33:33,011 --> 00:33:34,220
It was Murano.

492
00:33:36,431 --> 00:33:37,932
Murano?

493
00:33:38,016 --> 00:33:41,769
He said that he went
to ask the owner to release you.

494
00:33:42,895 --> 00:33:44,731
He confessed just now.

495
00:33:44,814 --> 00:33:46,983
Please let Miyuki go!

496
00:33:47,859 --> 00:33:49,652
Please, I beg you!

497
00:33:50,528 --> 00:33:52,155
Are you stupid?

498
00:34:14,510 --> 00:34:16,054
<i>But,</i>

499
00:34:16,137 --> 00:34:19,140
at that time, Kuriyama was not dead yet.

500
00:34:21,726 --> 00:34:24,937
He lost consciousness
because he was strangled,

501
00:34:25,021 --> 00:34:29,525
<i>and his breathing and pulse</i>
<i>became extremely weak.</i>

502
00:34:29,609 --> 00:34:32,070
<i>It's a so-called state of apparent death.</i>

503
00:34:33,446 --> 00:34:35,490
<i>Kuriyama regained consciousness</i>

504
00:34:35,573 --> 00:34:36,991
<i>exited the closet,</i>

505
00:34:37,075 --> 00:34:39,494
<i>and lost consciousness again.</i>

506
00:34:40,411 --> 00:34:43,414
<i>And then you came in.</i>

507
00:34:43,956 --> 00:34:45,416
<i>Seeing him like that,</i>

508
00:34:45,500 --> 00:34:49,587
<i>you mistakenly thought Kuriyama</i>
<i>had died from drinking the poison.</i>

509
00:34:49,670 --> 00:34:52,381
<i>However, Kuriyama,</i>
<i>who was still breathing,</i>

510
00:34:52,465 --> 00:34:54,717
<i>regained consciousness once more.</i>

511
00:34:54,801 --> 00:34:56,969
<i>And due to the consciousness disorder</i>

512
00:34:57,053 --> 00:34:59,722
<i>caused by the hypoxic state</i>
<i>from being strangled,</i>

513
00:34:59,806 --> 00:35:01,057
<i>he got your name…</i>

514
00:35:01,140 --> 00:35:02,225
Mari…

515
00:35:02,308 --> 00:35:03,726
<i>…wrong.</i>

516
00:35:03,810 --> 00:35:08,773
<i>That pushed you</i>
<i>to lay your hands on Kuriyama.</i>

517
00:35:10,066 --> 00:35:15,863
You and Murano both tried
to kill Kuriyama,

518
00:35:15,947 --> 00:35:18,825
and both of you failed.

519
00:35:19,492 --> 00:35:21,035
<i>However, in the end,</i>

520
00:35:21,953 --> 00:35:24,831
<i>you were the one who completed it.</i>

521
00:35:30,253 --> 00:35:31,712
Ms. Yanagihara,

522
00:35:32,296 --> 00:35:35,842
I am committing you to trial
on suspicion of murder.

523
00:35:41,472 --> 00:35:42,723
What about Murano?

524
00:35:43,599 --> 00:35:45,893
He will be charged with attempted murder.

525
00:35:47,770 --> 00:35:52,275
You hid the fact that you had entered
a relationship with Kaito Miura,

526
00:35:52,358 --> 00:35:56,779
and tried to get Murano
to kill the victim, didn't you?

527
00:35:56,863 --> 00:35:58,447
If only he wasn't here,

528
00:35:58,531 --> 00:36:01,534
I could be with the person I love forever.

529
00:36:03,035 --> 00:36:07,081
<i>But you got tired of Murano</i>
<i>never following through,</i>

530
00:36:07,790 --> 00:36:09,750
so you finally did it yourself.

531
00:36:10,918 --> 00:36:14,046
Yet coincidentally,
Murano followed through

532
00:36:14,839 --> 00:36:17,258
on the same day.

533
00:36:20,011 --> 00:36:22,138
I have a message from Murano.

534
00:36:22,972 --> 00:36:24,974
Please tell Miyuki this.

535
00:36:26,684 --> 00:36:28,186
This is my fault.

536
00:36:29,478 --> 00:36:31,314
I'm so sorry.

537
00:36:33,232 --> 00:36:34,066
But,

538
00:36:35,318 --> 00:36:38,362
let's both atone for our crimes

539
00:36:39,113 --> 00:36:40,198
and get married.

540
00:36:42,408 --> 00:36:44,619
I'll be waiting for her forever.

541
00:36:49,123 --> 00:36:51,250
You might have just been using him,

542
00:36:51,334 --> 00:36:53,461
but he was serious.

543
00:37:02,261 --> 00:37:04,180
Are you kidding me?

544
00:37:09,310 --> 00:37:11,395
Stupid useless man.

545
00:37:11,479 --> 00:37:13,940
Don't get ahead of yourself!

546
00:37:14,774 --> 00:37:20,905
It's because you failed to kill him
that I'm in this mess!

547
00:37:27,828 --> 00:37:28,663
And here…

548
00:37:35,544 --> 00:37:38,464
And here I thought
I could finally get out.

549
00:37:48,140 --> 00:37:49,433
Did you really…

550
00:37:52,311 --> 00:37:53,980
think that?

551
00:37:58,985 --> 00:38:00,444
You killed someone.

552
00:38:02,989 --> 00:38:05,616
Even if you managed to get out of this,

553
00:38:09,120 --> 00:38:10,579
by doing all this,

554
00:38:13,291 --> 00:38:14,875
did you really think

555
00:38:16,127 --> 00:38:17,795
you could move forward?

556
00:38:28,222 --> 00:38:29,307
Move forward?

557
00:38:32,893 --> 00:38:35,062
Why would you assume that?

558
00:38:37,064 --> 00:38:39,191
I never said anything about "forward."

559
00:38:41,319 --> 00:38:46,115
I just wanted to break away from the owner
and be with Kaito forever.

560
00:38:47,658 --> 00:38:49,493
I don't care about the future.

561
00:38:50,328 --> 00:38:53,039
As long as I'm happy now,
that's all that matters.

562
00:38:57,335 --> 00:38:58,919
Someone who's talented,

563
00:39:01,380 --> 00:39:03,591
has a good job,

564
00:39:05,760 --> 00:39:08,220
and lives without any hardship

565
00:39:10,514 --> 00:39:12,975
wouldn't understand my feelings.

566
00:39:17,521 --> 00:39:20,024
I even defaulted on my scholarship

567
00:39:20,983 --> 00:39:24,945
and used all the money I earned for Kaito.

568
00:39:31,702 --> 00:39:33,371
It was fun, though.

569
00:40:32,930 --> 00:40:34,056
I…

570
00:40:36,725 --> 00:40:38,853
didn't see anything.

571
00:40:49,572 --> 00:40:50,865
There are people

572
00:40:52,366 --> 00:40:54,618
in society waiting for help.

573
00:40:56,954 --> 00:41:01,167
I thought I was working for those people.

574
00:41:04,545 --> 00:41:06,255
But it was all just an ideal.

575
00:41:08,966 --> 00:41:11,760
I didn't see anything.

576
00:41:15,473 --> 00:41:18,684
Isn't it a good thing by itself
that you realized that?

577
00:41:30,196 --> 00:41:31,280
Hey.

578
00:41:31,947 --> 00:41:33,949
Your nose is running.

579
00:41:41,749 --> 00:41:42,917
Hey.

580
00:41:43,918 --> 00:41:45,127
You look ugly.

581
00:41:51,383 --> 00:41:53,219
Go on, cry.

582
00:42:08,734 --> 00:42:09,860
Ms. Kiryu.

583
00:42:09,944 --> 00:42:12,530
- Stamp this, please.
- Okay.

584
00:42:14,281 --> 00:42:17,493
Mark them all
as "by the end of today," please.

585
00:42:18,702 --> 00:42:19,870
- Okay.
- Okay.

586
00:42:23,582 --> 00:42:24,583
Wait.

587
00:42:25,376 --> 00:42:26,460
Dr. Honda…

588
00:42:29,880 --> 00:42:33,551
What does this LC-MS mean?

589
00:42:33,634 --> 00:42:34,760
What?

590
00:42:35,761 --> 00:42:38,931
Oh, it's the same as always,
so if you could just stamp it for now,

591
00:42:39,014 --> 00:42:39,890
No.

592
00:42:40,683 --> 00:42:41,934
As the supervisor,

593
00:42:42,017 --> 00:42:44,645
I want to really understand it
before I stamp it.

594
00:42:44,728 --> 00:42:45,771
Please tell me.

595
00:42:49,358 --> 00:42:50,734
Can't be helped…

596
00:42:51,318 --> 00:42:54,321
- I'm busy, you know?
- I'm sorry.

597
00:42:54,989 --> 00:42:56,740
Well, simply put,

598
00:42:56,824 --> 00:43:02,162
it means separating components
with LC and analyzing the mass.

599
00:43:03,622 --> 00:43:04,957
Analyzing mass?

600
00:43:05,040 --> 00:43:06,000
Yes.

601
00:43:06,083 --> 00:43:08,460
You mean like on a scale?

602
00:43:08,544 --> 00:43:09,587
No, like I said…

603
00:43:10,296 --> 00:43:11,297
More documents?

604
00:43:12,089 --> 00:43:13,132
For LC-MS,

605
00:43:13,215 --> 00:43:15,384
I recommend this book.

606
00:43:16,385 --> 00:43:17,428
Thank you very much.

607
00:43:19,930 --> 00:43:22,641
LC… Liquid Chromatography?

608
00:43:23,642 --> 00:43:25,102
So what is LC-MS?

609
00:43:25,185 --> 00:43:27,521
It's that instrument over there.

610
00:43:35,988 --> 00:43:39,158
A child suspected of being abused
was in an accident.

611
00:43:39,241 --> 00:43:40,409
<i>What kind of screaming?</i>

612
00:43:40,492 --> 00:43:41,327
Are you okay?

613
00:43:41,410 --> 00:43:43,912
In the middle of the night,
suddenly, like "wahh!"

614
00:44:48,227 --> 00:44:50,896
Subtitle translation by: Maslin F.
